    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2470820">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2470820">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2470820)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2470820">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hercules-rockefeller" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2314402); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2314402&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182413" alt="Hercules Rockefeller" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2314402)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hercules-rockefeller" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2314402); return false;" >Hercules Rockefeller</a></span> <span class="odate time_1457671024 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Mar 2016 04:37</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2470820">
									

<p>Don't stop this now, psul, I was having such a good time, I was having a ball! Beelzebub may have a devil put aside for me, but that won't stop me from upvoting. +1</p>
<p>I wasn't expecting the Eta-11 contest arc to end in such a humorous way, that was great - the first mission was pretty neat as well, I loved how inventive it was, but ultimately it's the last mission that steals the show (as I'm sure you meant it to). After all the feels and intensity of the previous entries, the goofiness of this one really came as a surprise, but it was a pleasant one - somehow, despite the change in tone from the rest of the series, this makes for a strangely appropriate ending, and an unexpectedly powerful one at that. And there's also the fact that you managed to make Eta-11 sing their every line without having the humor detract from their badassery. So, well done.</p>
<p>As an aside, the robots reminded me a lot of <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H4IbfEI6UfM">this</a> for some reason , only with Freddie Mercury's face.</p>
<p>But seriously, I just want to say to the entire Eta-11 contest team (WrongJohnSilver, psul, Smapti, CumaeanSibyl) how much I enjoyed reading your entries. I really felt like I was reading a body of work sprung from a single mind, so much did each tale or article fit in perfectly with the others, and so much were the quality of the writing and the ideas consistently excellent; each entry added something to the whole, and none felt unnecessary, or somehow lesser than the others. The cross-linking was absolutely seamless, to the point where it felt like those skips you were referencing had been written <em>for</em> Eta-11. And the <em>characters</em>&#8230; I actually feel like I know them a little now, and I have a clear mental image of each of them in my head, which is saying a lot when you consider that this is short fiction. To say I'm looking forward to reading more about them would be an understatement.</p>
<p>Anyway, I just wanted to say congrats on your success, and good luck in the contest!</p>

							</div>

								
