					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/littlesallydigby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1910986); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1910986&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182413" alt="LittleSallyDigby" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1910986)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/littlesallydigby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1910986); return false;" >LittleSallyDigby</a></span> <span class="odate time_1475333761 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Oct 2016 14:56</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2663722">
									

<p>Three parts, all excellent. Upvoted.</p>
<p>Some notes:</p>
<ul>
<li>The use of PoI designations feels right for Foundation documentation, but I think you could've done more to remind the out-of-universe reader who you're talking about. A quick parenthetical description of where the designation comes from, or encoding &quot;PoI-XXXX&quot; with a link to the document where the designation originates, would go a long way.</li>
<li>The pocket dimension in Theme and Variations felt like a video game I would like to play.</li>
<li>I don't know if this is a consensus thing or something the man himself had a preference on, but I've never seen the spelling &quot;Freddy Mercury&quot; outside of this tale- it's always been &quot;Freddie.&quot;</li>
<li>I understand if you don't want to write logs for Elegy after giving it its own tale, but &quot;no logs due to [the noise-canceling properties of the location]&quot; feels a bit off. I'm certain the Foundation would at least debrief the task force afterward, if not actually come up with a way to monitor/record what was being &quot;said&quot; during the mission- conducting any operation without at least trying to record what happened is extremely out of character for the organization. You could just change the current link text to something like &quot;for more information, see {Commander Richards's mission report}.&quot;</li>
</ul>

							</div>

								
					
