					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2156983&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182413" alt="psul" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2156983)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;" >psul</a></span> <span class="odate time_1476104255 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Oct 2016 12:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2668108">
									

<p>Thanks for the vote, and for the comments, LittleSallyDigby.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The use of PoI designations feels right for Foundation documentation, but I think you could've done more to remind the out-of-universe reader who you're talking about</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I've added Charles Mace's name to the Phase 2 report - I've already linked to his other appearances (in <a href="/scp-1638">SCP-1638</a> and <a href="/enjoy-the-silence">Enjoy the Silence</a>) in the text, so there's not much else to link to, but it's good to have a reminder, as Mace becomes important in <a href="/counterpoint">Counterpoint</a>, the next tale in the sequence.</p>
<p>The other two PoIs are newly created (I hesitate to call them characters, as they don't get any characterisation), so I don't have anything to link for them. I'd be delighted if anyone wanted to write some tales about them, however, and would definitely link to them in that case.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I've never seen the spelling &quot;Freddy Mercury&quot; outside of this tale- it's always been &quot;Freddie&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Quite right - fixed.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>You could just change the current link text to something like &quot;for more information, see {Commander Richards's mission report}.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is the trickiest for me. I didn't want to link to <a href="/enjoy-the-silence">Enjoy the Silence</a> as a mission report, as it's such a personal narrative for Hennessey. And in my headcanon, the reason that a report hasn't yet been filed is that the experience was emotional for all of them, and Commander Richards hasn't worked out how to file it. I've left it as &quot;Post-engagement report awaited&quot; for now.</p>

